<p>I have a question that is similar to <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/16223413/excel-random-number-from-a-set-of-options">this one</a>, but a little different:</p>  <p>Let's say I have data like this:</p>  <pre><code>CAR NAME   COLOR  LIST OF COLORS Car1         ?        Red Car2         ?        Blue Car3         ?        Green Car4         ?        Black </code></pre>  <p>and I want to randomly distribute all of the colors to all of the cars without repetition, i.e.</p>  <pre><code>CAR NAME   COLOR  LIST OF COLORS Car1       Green        Red Car2       Black        Blue Car3       Blue         Green Car4       Red          Black </code></pre>  <p>Is there a way to have a cell randomly select from a list excluding values already input in another range?</p>